Defendant Freddie Reynolds Jr in court.  Attorney Theodore OReilly in court for Freddie Reynolds Jr.  Attorney Jon R Josephsen Jr. in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court for Scheduling conference.  Defense has received discovery and an offer from the State and requests adjourned scheduling conference.  Case adjourned to Br. 9
Scheduling conference scheduled for November 23, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Freddie Reynolds Jr in court in person.  Attorney Theodore OReilly in court in person for Freddie Reynolds Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer B. Czapla. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 09. Court orders defendant to continue to comply with Justice Point conditions. 
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Freddie Reynolds in court with Attorney Theodore OReilly; both appear in person.  Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is on an active scene. Defendant is reminded to contine working with Justice Point. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 6, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Freddie Reynolds in court in person.  Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for preliminary hearing. States witness is present. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. State requests this matter be set in the trial court for a State V. Lee hearing; denied. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing. Case adjourned to Branch 17. Defendant is reminded by the Court to continue working with Justice Point.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 26, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and filed. Justice Point Supervision Report. Deputy Court Clerk: LVD

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Freddie Reynolds in court with attorney Theodore OReilly.  Defendant Freddie Reynolds in custody.  Lisa M Valenti-Jordan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Freddie Reynolds appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Stark, Branch 17.  AS TO COUNT 1:  Motion to dismiss by defense for lack of probable cause argued and DENIED by the Court.  AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2 "HABITUAL CRIMINALITY REPEATER" ENHANCER:  Motion to dismiss by the defense, argued and GRANTED by the Court.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.
